"3/7/1991--Introduced. Calls for the President to: (1) confer with Kuwait, other member nations of the coalition against Iraq, or the United Nations to establish an International Criminal Court or an International Military Tribunal to try and punish all individuals, including Saddam Hussein, involved in the planning or execution of specified war crimes and crimes against humanity in violation of international law; and (2) seek prompt and effective U.N. Security Council action to stop the use of chemical weapons and to punish those responsible."